== zlib ==
<pre>wget http://zlib.net/zlib-1.2.7.tar.gz
tar xvfz zlib-1.2.7.tar.gz
cd zlib-1.2.7
configure --prefix=/boot/common && make install</pre>

There will be an error, simply do

<pre>gcc -shared -O3  -fPIC -DHAVE_HIDDEN -o libz.so.1.2.7 adler32.lo crc32.lo deflate.lo infback.lo inffast.lo inflate.lo inftrees.lo trees.lo zutil.lo compress.lo uncompr.lo gzclose.lo gzlib.lo gzread.lo gzwrite.lo
make install
cd ..</pre>

and everything will be fine. This is the same command that triggers the error, only without "-lc" on the end.

